TextEquiv.Unicode: Conquestus est nobis venerabilis frater noster A. episcopus
sancti Asaph quod. cum ecclesia sancti Michaelis de Ken ad ecclesiam
suam iure parochiali pertineat, Menevensis episcopus ad eam dedicandam
Datierung nach den Jahren des Bischofs A(dam) von St. Asaph.
Ken - Keri, now Kerry in S. Montgomeryshire. The decretal evidently refers
to the dispute between the sees of St. Asaph and St. David's in which
Giraldus Cambrensis played a prominent part (Opera 1.32-9, 323 R.S.) See
Lloyd, History of Wales 1.559. Bishop Adam won his case at the Lateran
Council, 1179, but the decision was later reversed. The decretal may
refer to an attempt to enforce the decision of 1179.
